<br>
If we dont want to go back to Velious, we are going to need to email spam absor and anyone else who will listen with a petition demanding fixes. The most obvious and important fixes we will need are <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    pet bug/flexibility</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> related.:<br>
<br>
*<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Pets must become almost completely immune (75%) to ae damage</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->, all casters pets.<br>
<br>
*Mages must be given <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>raid pets which are completely imune (100%) to ae damage</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->. the pet will have low hp (1000) but will have rather high damage output<br>
<br>
*All <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>pets must be made to use their masters casting effectiveness level</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> (so procs/spells/taps will land)<br>
<br>
*All <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>pets must become included in group healing</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> and buffing spells<br>
<br>
*The <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>pet z-axis &amp; poofing bug must be addressed and fixed immediately.</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> Personally i think it has something to do with the pet being &quot;pushed off its path&quot; so to speak, and since it doesnt know &quot;what to do&quot;, it basically just poofs. If my suspsion is right just simply make the pet be transported to the ss of the zone with a wiped hate list should this happen, allowing for the master to summon it back.<br>
<br>
Before we even think about upgrades, these 5 long standing flexibility bugs are absolute necessities if we dont want the mage class to fall into uselessness in pop. <br>
<br>
Its every mages duty to write an email to absor highlighting the need for these 5 changes. these 5 changes are the difference between mages being absolutely useless and somewhat useful in pop.<br>
<br>
